%N A143453 Square array A(n,k) of numbers of length n ternary words with at least k 0-digits between any other digits (n,k >= 0), read by antidiagonals.
%H A143453 Alois P. Heinz, <a href="/A143453/b143453.txt">Rows n = 0..140, flattened</a>
%F A143453 G.f. of column k: 1/(x^k*(1-x-2*x^(k+1))).
%F A143453 A(n,k) = 3^n if k=0, else A(n,k) = 2*n+1 if n<=k+1, else A(n,k) = A(n-1,k) + 2*A(n-k-1,k).
%e A143453 A(3,1) = 11, because 11 ternary words of length 3 have at least 1 0-digit between any other digits: 000, 001, 002, 010, 020, 100, 101, 102, 200, 201, 202.
%e A143453 Square array A(n,k) begins:
